SUMMARY:Act Now for Solar: Strategies for Reducing Emissions and Lowering Energy Costs
DESCRIPTION:This event is being offered through the Jewish Climate Leadership Coalition\, which works to support Jewish community organizations to take climate action. All are welcome to join! \n\nThe best time to install solar is right now\, and the window is closing fast.\nJoin the Jewish Climate Leadership Coalition for an informative webinar.\nRegisterEvent DetailsAs a result of federal legislation passed in 2025 aimed at obstructing the deployment of clean energy technologies\, the tax and rebate incentives relating to solar energy are changing. New project requirements have gone into place as of January 1\, 2026 and will remain accessible through June 2026. \nDespite these challenges\, solar still is\, and will remain\, a cost-saving\, accessible\, and critical climate solution. At this program\, we will introduce you to our trusted partners who are poised to help you finance a solar installation in compliance with the new regulations and to take advantage of all incentives that your project is entitled to. Register now to learn how you can make the most of this closing window by putting your solar planning into urgent action.
URL:https://adamah.org/event/coalition-webinar-solar-projects-lower-energy-costs/
LOCATION:Virtual\, Zoom / Online
CATEGORIES:Coalition
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://adamah.org/wp-content/uploads/pearlstone-solar-edited-1.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260317T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260317T160000
