SUMMARY:Leading the Charge in Manhattan: Jewish Leadership and Climate Action
DESCRIPTION:Climate action starts locally—and Jewish institutions have a powerful role to play.\nRegisterEvent DetailsLeading the Charge: Manhattan brings together Jewish leaders\, lay leaders\, local environmental organizations\, and elected officials for an engaging\, practical conversation about climate action in the Manhattan.\nThe workshop will connect Jewish values with local policy\, community expertise\, and real-world examples to help institutions move from intention to action. \nHear from: \n\nMayor’s Office of Climate Justice – Ivy Trzebucki\nNew York League of Conservation Voters – Lea Giddins\nJewish Climate Action Network – Ana Levy-Lyons\nNew York City Council Member (District 2) – Harvey Epstein\n\nParticipants will explore: \n\nClimate priorities and challenges specific to Manhattan\nHow synagogues and Jewish organizations can reduce emissions\, save money\, and strengthen resilience\nLocal programs\, advocacy efforts\, and partners available now\nWhat peer institutions are already doing—and what’s possible next\n\nThe Brooklyn edition of this workshop featured Borough President Antonio Reynoso\, local environmental advocates\, and representatives from the Mayor’s Office of Climate Justice—and left participants energized and connected. We’re excited to build that same momentum in the Bronx. \n\n“This is how we build borough-wide resilience. The whole experience felt like being in a vibrant garden\, nourished and cross-pollinated by one another’s ideas.” – Antonio Reynoso
URL:https://adamah.org/event/leading-the-charge-in-manhattan/
LOCATION:Brotherhood Synagogue\, 28 Gramercy Park\, NY\, 10003
CATEGORIES:Coalition,New York
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://adamah.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/manhattan-aerial-view.jpg
END:VEVENT
