SUMMARY:Havdallah at the Observatory
DESCRIPTION:Registration for this event is free. Donations are welcome.  \nSay Goodby to Shabbat and Hello to the Night\nJoin Wilderness Torah at the Chabot Space and Science Center for an evening of ritual\, wonder\, and connection to the living cosmos. \nRegisterEvent DetailsGather with us as the sun sinks into the Bay and darkness gathers. Rooted in earth-based Jewish tradition\, we will mark the moment when three stars appear with havdallah\, saying goodbye to Shabbat and hello to the night. From there\, we turn our bodies and our blessings upward\, blessing the month’s new moon with a Kiddush Levana ritual. \nJoin Wilderness Torah at the Chabot Space and Science Center for an evening of ritual\, wonder\, and connection to the living cosmos. After the blessings\, there will be time to gaze into the heavens through Chabot’s three observatory telescopes\, experiencing the night sky as our ancestors once did\, with awe\, humility\, and gratitude.
URL:https://adamah.org/event/havdallah-at-the-observatory/
LOCATION:Chabot Space and Science Center\, 10000 Skyline Blvd\, Oakland\, California\, 94619
CATEGORIES:San Francisco Bay Area
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://adamah.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Adamah-SF-Havdallah.jpg
END:VEVENT
