SUMMARY:Youth Programs Discovery Nights
DESCRIPTION:Registration for these events are free. Donations are welcome. \n \n\n\n\nCome get a taste of Wilderness Torah Youth Programs with your kids \n\n\n\n\n\n\nThese preview nights are four chances throughout the spring for families like you to head outside and experience what makes our youth programs so special.\n \n\n\n\n\nEvent Details \n\n\n\nEach evening offers a hands-on nature activity rooted in earth-based Jewish wisdom\, creativity\, and skill-building. Come for just one\, or come for them all\, but be sure to explore whether Wilderness Torah Youth Programs are a good fit for your family.  \n\n\n\n\n \n\n\n\n Wednesday\, April 15\nFire Building and Tending Skills at Joaquin Miller Park\n(Ages 9–18)  \n\n\n\n\nRegister Now \n\n\n\nTuesday\, March 24\nStick Bread Over the Fire at Cesar Chavez Park\n(Ages 5–14) \n\n\n\n\nRegister Now \n\n\n\nThursday\, May 14\nMaking Oak Gall Ink at Lake Temescal\n(Ages 5-12) \n\n\n\n\nRegister Now \n\n\n\nMonday\, June 8\nNatural dye challah covers at Live Oak Park\n(Ages 5–12) \n\n\n\n\nRegister Now
URL:https://adamah.org/event/youth-programs-discovery-nights/
LOCATION:East Bay\, California
