SUMMARY:Jewish Green Business Network Summit at Climate Week SF
DESCRIPTION:Join Adamah’s Jewish Green Business Network at Climate Week SF for a high-level summit dedicated to the intersection of Jewish identity and climate leadership.  \nRegisterEvent DetailsWe are proud to convene a community of Jewish climate professionals\, founders\, philanthropists\, corporates and investors to advance climate innovation. \nAttendees will engage in discussions on current changes in business practices\, explore North American-Israeli green business collaborations\, and build intergenerational connections that empower the next generation of climate leaders. \nWhy Attend? \n\nCurated Networking: Connect in person with a supportive community that are ready to help one another succeed in a common mission.\nStrategic Collaboration: Learn about business opportunities and emerging technologies that accelerate the transition to a green economy.\nValues-Driven Leadership: In a time of funding cutbacks\, learn from inspiring speakers who align professional expertise with Jewish responsibility and global impact.\n\nWhether you are looking to scale your impact\, find strategic collaborators\, or anchor your professional journey in shared values\, this summit is the space to expand your network in a meaningful way.
URL:https://adamah.org/event/jewish-green-business-network-summit-at-climate-week-sf/
LOCATION:Monument\, 140 9th St\, San Francisco\, California\, 94103
CATEGORIES:Jewish Green Business Network,San Francisco Bay Area
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://adamah.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Summit.png
END:VEVENT
