SUMMARY:Roots and Resilience: Adamah NY Environmental Journey to Israel
DESCRIPTION:An opportunity for NY-based Jewish Climate and Sustainability Professionals\nAdamah NY is thrilled to announce a second fully funded\, weeklong trip to Israel in May 2026! \nApplication deadline has closedEvent Details \nNY-based experts and practitioners in the climate and sustainability fields—from business to nonprofits to government—are invited to apply for this exciting opportunity!\n\nOverviewItineraryApplyOverview \nTrip Dates: May 4-10\, 2026\nThis tour offers an immersive introduction to Israel’s social\, political\, religious\, and geostrategic complexities\, with a focused exploration of its environmental challenges and innovative solutions. Participants will engage with leading Israeli and Palestinian scientists\, activists\, entrepreneurs\, and policymakers in the climate and sustainability fields\, providing a comprehensive understanding of Israel’s approach to these critical issues. \nThe tour highlights three key areas:\n\nClimate and Sustainability Movement: Learn about Israel’s environmental efforts and build relationships with Israeli-based climate and environmental professionals to foster collaboration and shared learning.\nClimate Innovation and Technology: Gain insights into Israel’s thriving climate tech sector and its cutting-edge advancements.\nEnvironmental Peacebuilding: Explore initiatives promoting shared society and cooperation through environmental projects.\n\nTarget Audience\nNY-based Jewish environmentalists and professionals working in climate and sustainability across sectors—including nonprofits\, business\, government\, higher education\, Jewish education\, and more. If you’re unsure whether you fit the criteria\, please reach out! \nThis tour will deepen participants’ understanding of Israel’s internal and external socio-political dynamics\, its pioneering environmental strategies\, and the potential lessons applicable to New York as it navigates rapid development\, population growth\, and the challenges of climate mitigation and adaptation. \n\nRead about the 2025 Roots and Resilience Journey to Israel or view the full itinerary. \nContact: Dr. Shahar Sadeh\, Adamah NY Director at shahar.sadeh@adamah.org.\n\nItinerary \nItinerary and Points of Interest\nThe tour runs from Monday\, May 4th (12 PM) through Sunday\, May 10th (9 PM). This accommodates for late-night flights from Israel to arrive back in NYC by 6 AM on May 11th. \nWhile the full itinerary is still being finalized\, the program promises a fast-paced\, enriching week packed with visits\, meetings\, and meaningful experiences. The group will explore major strategic\, holy\, natural\, and cultural sites\, including West and East Jerusalem\, the Jordan Rift Valley and Dead Sea region\, Arad\, North and West Negev Desert (featuring a visit to a sustainable Bedouin community)\, Jaffa\, and Tel Aviv. \nWe will also visit the Nova Festival site and key locations related to the October 7th massacre. \nShabbat will be spent in Tel Aviv. \nExplore the 2025 full itinerary.\n\nApply \nApplication Process\nApplications are accepted on a rolling basis\, and spots are expected to fill quickly. Be prepared to include a short bio (up to 250 words) and headshot\, no later than January 25th. Acceptance letters will be sent by Feb 1st. \nApplication window has closed\n\nFees\, Commitment\, and Expectations\nThe tour in Israel is free and fully funded by Adamah NY thanks to the generous support of UJA Federation of NY and private donations. It will be covering travel within Israel\, kosher meals\, site visits\, double-occupancy accommodations\, and medical insurance. \n\nParticipants are responsible for booking and covering their flights to/from Israel and travel insurance.\nSingle-room lodging is available for an additional cost. Applicants from the nonprofit sector may be eligible to apply for modest flight subsidies based on financial need.\nTo secure your spot\, a $750 refundable registration fee is required upon acceptance. This fee will be refunded upon completion of the tour and a post-trip survey.\nParticipants are expected to participate in a pre-departure meeting on April 20th\, 5:30-8 p.m.\, in Manhattan (location TBD) as well as a post-tour dinner in June (time and location TBA).\n\n\nsponsored by
URL:https://adamah.org/event/adamah-ny-environmental-journey-to-israel/
LOCATION:Israel\, Israel
CATEGORIES:Coalition,New York
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://adamah.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/NY-Journey-to-Israel-2025-tour-participants.jpg
END:VEVENT
