SUMMARY:Adamah Brooklyn B’Mitzvah Cohort
DESCRIPTION:5 Sessions | 1.5 or 2 hours each\nHybrid Program: 1 virtual session + 4 in-person\, see schedule for details \n\n\n \nGive your child’s coming-of-age celebration deeper meaning\nConnect their Jewish identity to the sacred responsibility of caring for our earth \nApply by May 3 \nThis cohort-style program is open to students from all Jewish backgrounds in Brooklyn who are interested in working in community on the issue of climate.\nStudents in the year leading up to their B’Mitzvah or who have completed their B’Mitzvah in the past year and still want to complete a mitzvah project are welcome to apply. \nInterested in bringing this program to another area of New York City\, Long Island or Westchester? Reach out to Hannah (Hannah.glass@adamah.org)! \n\nJewish Environmental LearningHands-on Climate Action & Service WorkOne-on-One SupportOverviewProgram DetailsCohort ScheduleB’Mitzvah Add-OnsOverview \nPlanning a B’Mitzvah can feel overwhelming.\nBetween logistics and preparation\, it’s easy to lose sight of the deeper meaning of coming of age in Jewish tradition—and to make time for joy along the way. While a mitzvah project can tackle so many issues\, today’s youth are passionate about climate justice and the way it acts as an intersection of many social causes. We’re here to help channel that energy into a meaningful Mitzvah Project. \nThe Adamah Brooklyn B’Mitzvah Cohort empowers young people to design a mitzvah project that brings their values and responsibility to life.\nThis month-long environmental and social justice program\, taught by Adamah NY—a leading Jewish environmental organization—connects Jewish tradition with climate action. Through engaging learning\, hands-on service\, and personalized guidance\, participants create impactful environmental mitzvah projects\, deepen their commitment to social responsibility\, and gain the tools and confidence to take Jewishly rooted action throughout their lives—all while building community with like-minded peers. Participants will leave the program with a comprehensive mitzvah project\, including a fundraiser for Adamah NY’s local Climate Justice work. \nWhy this is for you!\nStudents will gain deep knowledge of Jewish environmentalism\, an introduction to various climate organizations in NYC\, experience with hands-on volunteering\, as well as hard fundraising and community organizing skills. You will receive support in accomplishing a mitzvah project and integrating your learnings into the B’Mitzvah experience – through D’var Torah or in other aspects of the celebration. \nProgram Details \nDetails\nStructure\nThe cohort will meet 5 times and each session will engage with a different area of Jewish environmental connection and climate action. We will explore action through direct service on an urban farm\, meet with climate leaders in the field\, and learn and practice fundraising skills. Students will not just be learning but will put these lessons into action – fundraising and developing a mitzvah project of their own. Participants will also have the chance to meet one-on-one for support with project implementation from Hannah\, the program facilitator. \nOur Educators\nClasses will be taught by Adamah NY’s Jewish Environmental Educator\, Hannah Kahn Glass. Hannah draws from a background in both formal and experiential Jewish education\, Jewish farming\, and community organizing. Students will also learn from guest speakers and other Adamah NY staff members. \nFees\nThe cost of the program is $500. Part of the student’s mitzvah Project will be to fundraise for a social justice cause. We encourage fundraising to support Adamah NY’s Jewish Environmental Justice work. \nCohort Schedule \nCohort Schedule\nMonday\, May 11: 6-7:30pm\nMonday\, May 18: 6:30-7:30pm on Zoom\nSunday\, May 31: 2-4pm\nMonday\, June 8: 6:30-7:30pm\nSunday\, June 14: 2-4pm \n\nIn-person location TBA\n\nB’Mitzvah Add-Ons \nB’Mitzvah Add-Ons\nLooking for more ways to bring Adamah into your B’Mitzvah celebration? We offer add-on opportunities to deepen your simcha’s connection to environmental Judaism. \n\nSustainable Simcha Consultation – meet for a one-hour session with our climate action team for coaching on ways to make your students’ B’Mitzvah service and party eco-friendly.\nBring Adamah NY to your B’nai Mitzvah Party to lead an eco-activity. Options include an herbalism station\, flower-pressing crafts\, native seedball making\, and more!\nInterested in holding your Simcha at our retreat center? Participants of the program are eligible to receive a discount at Isabella Freedman or Pearlstone Retreat Centers.\n\n\nApply \nReach out to Adamah NY’s Education & Community Engagement Coordinator Hannah Kahn Glass at hannah.glass@adamah.org with any questions.
URL:https://adamah.org/event/bmitzvah-cohort/
LOCATION:NYC\, New York\, NY
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://adamah.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Adamah-Teens-in-NYC-park.png
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR